    <text>
        <body>
            <div style="handwritten" type="letter">
                <head type="title">Miklós Oláh to Cornelis De Schrijver (Brussels, 1 August
                    1535)</head>
                <floatingText type="regesta">
                    <body>
                        <p>He was doubly happy that Cornelis De Schrijver sent Topographia to him:
                            on the one hand, for the love this shows towards him and also because he
                            can picture Rome this way. He will return the favor as soon as he can;
                            he will gladly recommend him to Cornelis de Schepper’s and Wolfgang
                            Haller’s attention. Frans van Cranevelt has sent Basil of Caesera’s work
                            in his own Latin translation to Oláh – Oláh is now sending it to him so
                            he can read it. </p>
                    </body>
                </floatingText>
                <pb/>
                <p>Nicolai Olai ad Cornelium Graphaeum Antverpiensem.</p>
                <p><hi rend="italic">Topographiam veteris Romae</hi>, quam ad me, Doctissime
                    Cornelii, dono misisti,<note type="critic">Ep.
                        544.</note><ref>/o:olahus.tei.15350727_1</ref> nudiustertius accepi. Quae
                    duplici nomine fuit mihi gratissima, primum, quod tuum in me candidum amorem,
                    quem nuper verbis declararas, nunc re ipsa cognoverim, tum quod Urbis, totius
                    orbis dominae, veterem <milestone unit="pb"/>illam maiestatem et insignem
                    magnificentiam perlecto ipso libello ob oculos iam ponere possim. Habeo igitur
                    tibi, mi Graphaee, gratias, quas possum cumulatas, qui me in amicorum tuorum
                    numerum inscribere meque hoc tuo munusculo honorare volueris. Non ero tuorum in
                    me officiorum et amoris immemor, sed eodem, quo tu me, amicitiae et
                    necessitudinis officio sum te prosecuturus, huncque Olaum talem semper in te et
                    tuos cognosces, qualem amor noster mutuus postulaverit. Quod me <del
                        corresp="Olahus">petit</del><add corresp="Olahus" type="corr">petis</add>,
                    ut <persName>Cornelio Sceppero</persName>, <persName>Volffgango
                        Hallero</persName>,<note type="critic">Wolfgang Haller.</note> quaestori
                    reginae, amicis communibus te commendem, etsi es, ut id satis scio, ob ingentem
                    tuam virtutem et doctrinam excellentem eis satis commendatus, tamen, ut iubes,
                    faciam id diligenter. Et neque in hac, neque in aliis multo maioribus rebus meam
                    unquam operam, quam quidem tibi gratam fore sensero, patiar a te desiderari.
                        <persName>Franciscus Craneveldius</persName>,<note type="critic">Frans van
                        Cranevelt.</note> amicus meus singularis hunc ad me misit
                        <persName>Basilii</persName><note type="critic">Basil of Caesarea.</note>
                    libellum a se Latinitate donatum, quem, ut perlegas, ad te misi. Vale et me, ut
                    coepisti, ama. </p>
                <p><placeName>Bruxellae</placeName> Kalendis Augusti 1535.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
